ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is an entry-level course to data mining, with a mathematical perspective. I would recommend it to someone who want a really, really light workload.

Wasn't data-mining as I had expected (was expecting more in the vein of mapreduce). Rather, it focuses on how large datasets were handled way back when. Seemed to redo many things that Matlab has already implemented in the same way that Matlab does things.
It is a really good course

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Data Mining is increasing important in modern information technology. I learned a couple of mathematical algorithms that may apply to my own research interest.
data mining will be helpful for social network data analysis which is my research area.
